Q: What are Services in Android and their types?
●  A Service is an Android component used to perform long-running tasks in the
   background.
●  It does not have a user interface.
●  It can keep running even if the user switches to another app.
Example:  Playing music, downloading files, tracking  location in the background.

Q: Why use a Service?
●  To run background tasks  without blocking the UI  .
●  Useful for tasks that need to run  continuously or  independently  .
●  Keeps running  even when the user leaves the app  (based  on the service type).

Types of Services in Android:
a) Foreground Service
b) Background Service
c) Bound Service

Background Service
●  Runs  without user interaction or notification  .
●  Used for  less important tasks  .
●  From Android 8 (API 26+), background services have restrictions.
●  Recommended to use  "WorkManager"  for such tasks.
Example:  Auto-sync, sending logs in the back   ground.
